      "profileHref": "/country/usa/congress/brad-sherman",
      "text": "In California, ballots are valid if mailed by Election Day, even if received a week later. Virtually all ballots are counted by then. Officials have a month to deal with a tiny number of questionable ballots. It’s careful, accurate, and honest. (3/4)",
